did.unittitle: Cayuga and Oswego Counties Legal Documents
did.abstract: The collection of legal documents contains deeds, government appointments, a list of Grand Jurors, and a Writ of Subpoena produced in counties of Oswego and Cayuga in the 19th century.

repository.corpname: State University of New York at Oswego

accessrestrict.p: Collection is open to the public.

bioghist.p: The Cayuga and Oswego County governments regulate the legal proceedings which occur in their county districts.

scopecontent.p: The collection of legal documents contains deeds, government appointments, a list of Grand Jurors, and a Writ of Subpoena produced in counties of Oswego and Cayuga in the 19th century.

userestrict.p: Please contact SUNY Oswego Archives and Special Collections for use restrictions.
